  "title": "Quantity Surveyor (Electrical / Contractual) | Woodlands | Up $6K",
  "description": "<p>Are you a detail-driven professional with a knack for numbers and a passion for construction? We’re looking for a <strong>Quantity Surveyor</strong>!</p><p>This is your opportunity to play a key role in shaping high-impact projects while ensuring cost efficiency and quality delivery.</p><p>💡 <strong>What You’ll Be Doing</strong></p><ul><li><p>Prepare <strong>accurate cost estimates</strong> for M&E systems (HVAC, electrical, plumbing, fire protection).</p></li><li><p>Support <strong>project costing</strong> and <strong>budget planning</strong> from start to finish.</p></li><li><p>Assist in <strong>tender preparation</strong> and evaluation for M&E works.</p></li><li><p>Work closely with project teams to identify <strong>cost-saving opportunities</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Conduct <strong>site measurements</strong> and manage interim valuations.</p></li><li><p>Evaluate <strong>variations and change orders</strong>, providing cost analysis and justifications.</p></li><li><p>Support contract management for all M&E-related work.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with engineers, architects, and contractors to align costs with project goals.</p></li><li><p>Identify and mitigate <strong>project risks</strong> associated with M&E works.</p></li></ul><p>✅ <strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></p><ul><li><p>Degree/Diploma in <strong>Quantity Surveying</strong>, <strong>Construction Management</strong>, <strong>M&E Engineering</strong>, or equivalent.</p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>3 years of relevant experience</strong> in the construction industry (M&E experience is a strong plus!).</p></li><li><p>Skilled in <strong>cost estimation</strong> and analysis.</p></li><li><p>Strong attention to detail with <strong>excellent analytical skills</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Team player with solid <strong>communication and interpersonal abilities</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Self-motivated, able to work both independently and collaboratively.</p></li></ul><p>📩 <strong>Why Join Us?</strong></p><ul><li><p>Be part of exciting, large-scale construction projects</p></li><li><p>Work in a dynamic and supportive team environment</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to grow your career in a specialized and in-demand field</p></li><li></li></ul><p><strong>How to Apply</strong></p><p>Send your updated CV to <a href=\"mailto:deborah@crew.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>deborah@crew.sg</strong></a> with:</p><ul><li><p>Your expected salary</p></li><li><p>Last drawn package</p></li><li><p>Notice period / earliest start date</p></li></ul><p>Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</p><p><br /><strong>Ho Yu Qing Deborah (R1104551)</strong><br />CREW by HRnet | HRnet Ventures Pte Ltd<br />EA Licence: <strong>24C2435</strong></p>",
